    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Paint coatings that have a characteristic intumescence when exposed to high heat. A foaming or bubbling layer forms in the paint layer that insulates the material beneath, protecting it from reaching a flash point. This type of paint may be based on silicone, casein, borax, polyvinyl chloride, urea formaldehyde or other substances.</Note_Text>
